description.narrative: The development objective of the Project is to improve the reliability and efficiency of the power system in Java-Bali and strengthen PLN and PGN's management capabilities.

title.narrative: Increased dispatch capability of generation units in East Java

baseline.value: Around 2000 MW of dispatch capability in 2002

target.value: Additional 2000 MW of dispatch capability by project closing date.

actual.value: Dispatch capability of generation units in east Java has been increased.

comment.narrative: Dispatch capability of generation units in east Java has been increased. However, the main benefit of the increased dispatch fromthe Grati steam plant to South Surabaya S/S (and corresponding reduction of the oil fired generation at Gresik) has notmaterialized yet due to the delay in the construction of the transmission line from Grati to South Surabaya

title.narrative: Natural Gas Pricing and PGN's restructuring and partial privatization studies completed

baseline.value: Natural Gas Pricing and PGN's restructuring and partial privatization have not been undertaken

target.value: Natural Gas Pricing and PGN's restructuring and partial privatization studies completed.

title.narrative: ERP system deployed to entire Java-Bali System after completing initial pilot roll-out

baseline.value: PLN does not employ ERP system

title.narrative: Progress report on PLN TA - Supplemental Study on Upper Cisokan Pump Storage Project
Progress on TA studies for PGN

target.value: TA studies completed by project closing date

comment.narrative: PGN has also completed training activities and remaining unused loan balance has been canceled.

title.narrative: Improved voltages at key 150kV substations in southeastern Java

baseline.value: The majority of key 150kV substations voltages are operating at 90% of capacity, or at 135kV in 2002

target.value: The majority of key 150kV substations voltages are operating at 100% of capacity.

actual.value: System voltages in project areas have improved and exact information is being collected.

comment.narrative: According to the loading level of 150/20kV substations, system voltages in southern Java have improved.

title.narrative: Reduced substation loadings at key Java-Bali 500kV and 150kV substations

baseline.value: The majority of substations have loadings at 80% of the capacity or more in 2002

target.value: The majority of substations have loadings at 50%-60% of the capacity.

actual.value: All substation works under the project are complete.

comment.narrative: Average substation loading of four 500/150kV inter-bus transformers is reduced to around 60%. And average loading of 150/20kVtransformers is around 70%. Java-Bali system retains appropriate reliability level according to precise quantitative information onsubstations.

title.narrative: Implementation milestones and the commissioning dates of 150kV substation expansions and uprated lines

actual.value: All substation expansions have been accomplished. However, the construction of five lines is delayed due to issues with landacquisition from private landowners, and with obtaining Ministry of Forestry's clearances.

comment.narrative: Most of the substation expansions have been accomplished and the 150 kV line in East Java has been completed. However, theconstruction of five transmission lines are delayed due to issues with land acquisition from private landowners, and with obtainingMinistry of Forestry's clearances.

title.narrative: Implementation milestones and the commissioning dates of 500kV substation expansions

actual.value: South Surabaya substation awaiting completion of transmission line.

comment.narrative: The four west Java and Jakarta substations are now completed as required. The energizing of the South Surabaya substation is heldup pending the completion of the Grati-South Surabaya line being funded through export credit from France.

title.narrative: PLN issues reconciled financial statements for the Java-Bali System within 45 days upon the completion of the fiscal year

target.value: 45 days since ERP fully deployed in Java-Bali System

comment.narrative: Target was achieved in 2013. Financial statements were thereafter recast based on revised parameters under ISAK 8 "Determiningwhether an arrangement contains a lease."
